 Orie, Reid also found herself on the end of a contentious verdict against a vastly experienced opponent who is the current IBA world heavyweight champion.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosie_M._Banks\", \"score\": 0.8664085269677004, \"rank\": 0.1516750654885949, \"text\": \"Rosie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosie_M._Banks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosie_M._Banks\"}, {\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eccles_Line\", \"score\": 0.9999971448676037, \"rank\": 2.1760876878617312e-06, \"text\": \"Eccles\", \"types\": [\"Q728937\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eccles_Line\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eccles_Line\"}, {\"begin\": 1057, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9285079603244342, \"rank\": 0.07676929253311655, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Reid\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"a contentious verdict\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"a vastly experienced opponent\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reid boxed superbly from the centre of the ring to take the opening round all five judges' cards before Mardi fought back to effectively level going into the last.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Reid\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1094}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"the ring\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening round\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1163}, {\"ngram\": \"all five judges' cards\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"Mardi\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was always going to be a tall order for Reid to come out on top in a final three-minute showdown but she arguably landed the cleaner work through her taller opponent's guard and could count herself unfortunate to drop the verdict.\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1488, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tall order\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"Reid\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"a final three-minute showdown\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"the cleaner work\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"her taller opponent's guard\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"the verdict\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevertheless it was a performance to be proud of by Reid, a former celebrated junior who only returned to the sport in April last year after six years out due to degenerative disc disease.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a performance\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"Reid\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"a former celebrated junior\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1614}, {\"ngram\": \"degenerative disc disease\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reid cut a philosophical figure in the mixed zone, refusing to blame bad luck for a series of decisions that privately GB chiefs believe ought not to have gone against them.\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1799, \"end\": 1801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gigabyte\", \"score\": 0.5048875459231532, \"rank\": 0.7493148486484867, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.